data.title: Cheryl Fernandez-Versini previews first track from her new album Only Human
data.meta_description: Cheryl Fernandez-Versini has given her fans a treat for the ears by serving up...
data.text:
Cheryl Fernandez-Versini has given her fans a treat for the ears by serving up the title track from her new album, Only Human, as a preview song.

The singer and X Factor judge released the number to those who pre-ordered her album, which is scheduled for release on 10 November. But thanks to the internet, you can hear it here:

She said of her fourth studio album that it’s the best work she’s ever put out, explaining: “I feel, for me, it’s my best work for many reasons.

“Looking back on everything that I’ve experienced personally, I think Only Human is a record that says, ‘Have fun, we’re only human, fight on when things go bad 'cos it’s going to be fine again’.”

Cheryl added: “I’m proof of that and for people who have seen things I might have been through, they will know how much this means to me.”

The 31-year-old former Girls Aloud star also posted the track listing for her new LP on Instagram, with her first single from the record – _Crazy Stupid Lov_e – sitting at number four.

Other tracks include Live Life Now, It’s About Time, Throwback, Stars, I Won’t Break and – incredibly – Tattoo, which HAS to be about her floral butt tatt, right?

With Only Human set for release about five weeks before the end of The X Factor, we could have another Alexandra Burke sitch on our hands, especially if Cheryl’s offering outperforms whoever goes on to win the talent series. WE CAN’T WAIT.
